1 What is Python ? 
Python is an interpreted, high-level, general-purpose programming language. Created by Guido van Rossum and first released in 1991.

2.What are the ways to install python
you can install directly from the python offical website or you can even download IDE tools or tools such as ANACONDA or PYCHARM etc. 

3. What are the Enviroments ? 
Its a sustained container where you can write/comple code and see the output.

4. Types?
 there are 3 types of code environment. (a. text editor  b. Integrated development environment 3. Notebook book environment )
